comments.body:
{code}
LD_DEBUG=all python -c 'import pyarrow'
{code}

shows that {{libparquet.so}} is trying to load {{libboost_regex.so.1.65.1}}:

{code}
     18209:	file=libboost_regex.so.1.65.1 [0];  needed by /home/phillip/miniconda3/envs/py36/lib/python3.6/site-packages/pyarrow/../../../libparquet.so.1 [0]
{code}

so this doesn't appear to be an issue with Arrow per se.

[~cpcloud] with build number 0 it works 

{code}
conda install parquet-cpp=1.4.0=0 -c conda-forge
{code}

[~cpcloud] locally building parquet-cpp-feedstock with 
{code}
conda build recipe
{code}
picks up the right arrow-cpp version, however running it with
{code}
conda build recipe -m .ci_support/osx_.yaml
{code}
reproduces the wrong version seen on the online builds.

I've got confused, what's the correct version of boost-cpp now? 1.67?

With fresh install:
{code}
arrow-cpp                 0.9.0                    py36_7    conda-forge
boost-cpp                 1.66.0                        1    conda-forge
{code}
